    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe assertion\n\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/src/nvim/drawline.c#L1126\n\nis failing under certain circumstances, which leads to Neovim closing unexpectedly.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```lua\n-- minimal.lua\n\n-- any non empty value works, I think\nvim.o.winbar = \"%f\"\n\nlocal go_win = function(winid)\n\tlocal winnr = vim.api.nvim_win_get_number(winid)\n\tvim.cmd.wincmd({ args = { \"w\" }, count = winnr })\nend\n\nvim.cmd.split({\n\tmods = { vertical = false, split = \"botright\" },\n})\nlocal winid = vim.api.nvim_get_current_win()\n\nvim.cmd.split({ mods = { vertical = true, split = \"belowright\" } })\ngo_win(winid)\n\nvim.api.nvim_set_option_value(\"winfixheight\", true, { scope = \"local\", win = 0 })\nvim.api.nvim_win_set_height(0, 8)\n``` \n \n1. `nvim --clean -u minimal.lua`\n2. `q:`\n3. The assertion fails and Neovim closes\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe assertion shouldn't fail\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.0 Build type: RelWithDebInfo LuaJIT 2.1.1741730670 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nDoesn't apply\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch latests\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm 20240203-110809-5046fc22\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nwezterm\n\n### Installation\n\n`sudo pacman -Syu neovim`",
